# Publication-Quality Chart Standards

This project uses **Apache ECharts** for all visualizations following Nature Research publication guidelines.

## Quick Reference

**Library**: ECharts (via `render_echarts()`) | **Fallback**: Plotly
**Colors**: Use `SCIENTIFIC_COLORS` palette from `user_profile_tab.py`
**Style**: Age-stratified norms, reference zones, EWMA trends, scientific citations

## Key Requirements

1. **Every chart MUST have**: Title, subtitle (methodology), axis labels with units, legend, tooltip
2. **Reference zones**: Shaded bands for normal ranges (using stacked area technique)
3. **Trend lines**: 7-day EWMA smoothing for time series
4. **Citations**: Evidence-based references below each chart
5. **Export**: SVG, PDF, PNG (300+ DPI), HTML, CSV/JSON

## Standard Heights

| Type | Height |
|------|--------|
| Line/Bar | 380px |
| Gauge | 280px |
| Radar | 280px |

## Color Semantics

| Meaning | Color |
|---------|-------|
| Good/Low Risk | `#27ae60` (green) |
| Normal | `#3498db` (blue) |
| Caution | `#f39c12` (yellow) |
| Poor/High Risk | `#e74c3c` (red) |
| Trend | `#2c3e50` (dark gray) |

